{"change_summary":"Rejected dot-prefixed milestone IDs so milestone data cannot collide with the `.locks` namespace, tightened task-run completion so a supplied `run_id` only finalizes an exact matching attempt, and changed new named retries after a stale legacy runless start to mark that older attempt as superseded before appending the retry. Added regressions covering the new ID validation, exact-match completion rejection, and legacy-open retry supersession behavior.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction; milestone-scoped locking and replay-safe updates mitigate this, but a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage.","Malformed or manually edited lineage can still contain multiple simultaneous runless open attempts for the same bead/project; the normal start path now prevents stale legacy-open contradictions for new named retries, but deterministic finalization of already-corrupt data still depends on repair or richer caller metadata."],"steps":[{"description":"Inspected the pending amendments against the current milestone model, service, and filesystem lineage logic to isolate the remaining lock-namespace, completion-targeting, and stale-open retry behaviors.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Updated `MilestoneId::new()` to reject dot-prefixed identifiers and extended the milestone-model tests to cover hidden-name rejection.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Patched `FsTaskRunLineageStore` so named completions no longer fall back to a lone runless open row, and so starting a new named retry after a stale legacy runless attempt first auto-fails the older attempt as superseded.","order":2,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Adjusted milestone-record service regressions for the new retry semantics, added an exact-match completion failure test, and reran formatting, milestone-record tests, and clippy validation.","order":3,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 103 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}